cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work or the Thai sarcasm gold set, please cite it as below."
title: "Cost-Aware Multi-Agent LLM Evaluation for Thai Sarcasm Detection"
authors:
  - name: "Thanaphumi (Thanaphumi2006)"
type: software
repository-code: "https://github.com/Thanaphumi2006/Cost-Aware-Multi-Agent-LLM-Evaluation-for-Thai-Sarcasm-Detection"
license: MIT
date-released: 2026-07-19
version: "1.0.0"
abstract: >-
  An empirical study of whether multi-agent LLM systems justify their cost on
  Thai sarcasm detection. Five systems (single agent, two-agent pipeline,
  three-agent debate, four-agent hybrid, and a free local model) are compared
  on a 127-item human-labeled gold set with paired bootstrap and McNemar's
  test, measuring F1, cost, latency, and API calls. Main finding: a single
  cheap model reading its own confidence statistically ties multi-agent
  systems costing up to 11x more.
keywords:
  - thai-nlp
  - sarcasm-detection
  - llm-evaluation
  - multi-agent-systems
  - cost-aware-ml
